  "dateModified": "2025-12-31",
  "datePublished": "2025-12-31",
  "description": "A hand is the set of cards currently held by a player as private information in a card game. The hand is the player\u0026rsquo;s primary resource: it defines what actions are available, what combinations are possible, and what information the player holds that opponents don\u0026rsquo;t. In poker, the hand is what you are betting on. In a trick-taking game, the hand is the sequence of plays you have available across an entire round.\n",
